# Symfony / Node envs (root + per-app) — only .env.example, apps/api/.env
# and apps/api/.env.test (placeholder-only templates) are committed.
#
# AUD-010 — `.env` alone matches the file *named* `.env` but NOT
# environment-specific files like `.env.dev` / `.env.prod`, which carry real
# secrets. `.env.dev` slipped into git that way (AUD-005). `.env.*` below
# closes the gap by ignoring every `.env.<suffix>`; the `!` allowlist lines
# re-include the deliberate templates (order matters — negations come last).
# Real per-environment secrets belong in untracked `.env.dev` / `.env.local`.
.env
.env.*
.env.local
.env.local.php
.env.*.local
!.env.example
!apps/api/.env
!apps/api/.env.test
!*.dist
!*.example

